# Personal Agent Conventions

## Task File Location

Task files live at `~/.agent/tasks/<repo>/<branch>/`. Resolve automatically:

```bash
REPO=$(basename $(git rev-parse --show-toplevel))
BRANCH=$(git branch --show-current)
TASK_DIR=~/.agent/tasks/$REPO/$BRANCH
```

Create the directory if it doesn't exist: `mkdir -p $TASK_DIR`

## Before Any Task

1. Read `$TASK_DIR/SPEC.md` if it exists
2. Read `$TASK_DIR/PROGRESS.md` if resuming
3. If no SPEC.md exists and the task is non-trivial, draft one using `~/.agent/_SPEC_TEMPLATE.md`

## PROGRESS.md Protocol

Update `$TASK_DIR/PROGRESS.md` after every meaningful step. Required fields:

```markdown
## Status: IMPLEMENTING
## Phase: spec → implement → diff-review → commit → push → pr-comments → done
## Current: implement
## Next: diff-review

## Done
- [x] completed item

## In Progress
- [ ] current item

## Blockers
- (none)

## Next Step
What to do next in one sentence.
```

## Journal

`~/.agent/JOURNAL.md` is the personal learning log. Never modify it without being asked.

## Spec Template

`~/.agent/_SPEC_TEMPLATE.md` is the reusable starting point for new specs.
